--- pakku.ORIG/src/pakku-0.17/doc/pakku.conf.5.txt	2026-07-07 08:49:47.463250887 -0700
+++ pakku/src/pakku-0.17/doc/pakku.conf.5.txt	2026-07-07 08:44:43.713505003 -0700
@@ -91,11 +91,14 @@
 *AllowedAurMaintainers =* maintainer ...::
 	A whitelist of approved AUR maintainers. Multiple maintainers are separated
 	by spaces, and the option may be repeated on several lines to accumulate
-	names. When this list is non-empty, pakku will not build or install any
-	AUR package (including dependencies) whose maintainer is missing, empty, or
-	not present in the list. The check is performed before any PKGBUILD or
-	included file is executed, so untrusted packages are never built. If the
-	list is empty or unset (the default), the check is disabled.
+	names. A trailing `# comment` on a line is stripped before the value is
+	used, so each maintainer can be annotated, e.g. `AllowedAurMaintainers =
+	maintainer1 # used for package foo`. When this list is non-empty, pakku
+	will not build or install any AUR package (including dependencies) whose
+	maintainer is missing, empty, or not present in the list. The check is
+	performed before any PKGBUILD or included file is executed, so untrusted
+	packages are never built. If the list is empty or unset (the default), the
+	check is disabled.
 
 See Also
 --------
